---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Click Speed Test — Free CPS Test | FastClickTest.com"
  description="Free online click speed test. Measure your CPS with a live graph, 7 test modes, score history and instant ratings. No signup needed."
  currentPage="home"
>
<div class="page">

  <div class="page-title">
    <h1>Click Speed <span class="hi">Test</span></h1>
    <p>Measure your CPS — clicks per second. Pick a mode, click the box, go.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="mode-selector">
    <button class="mode-btn" data-mode="1">1s</button>
    <button class="mode-btn active" data-mode="5">5s</button>
    <button class="mode-btn" data-mode="10">10s</button>
    <button class="mode-btn" data-mode="15">15s</button>
    <button class="mode-btn" data-mode="30">30s</button>
    <button class="mode-btn" data-mode="60">60s</button>
    <button class="mode-btn" data-mode="100" data-type="count">100 Clicks</button>
  </div>

  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat" id="stat-cps-card">
      <div class="stat-val" id="stat-cps">0.00</div>
      <div class="stat-lbl">CPS</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat-val" id="stat-timer">5.0</div>
      <div class="stat-lbl" id="stat-timer-lbl">Seconds</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat-val" id="stat-best">--</div>
      <div class="stat-lbl">Best CPS</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="click-area" class="idle">
    <div class="ca-idle" id="ca-idle">
      <div class="ca-cursor">🖱️</div>
      <div class="ca-text">Click Here to Start</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ca-running" id="ca-running">
      <div class="ca-big-num" id="ca-num">0</div>
      <div class="ca-sub">clicks</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p id="status-text">Select a mode above — timer starts on your first click</p>

  <div class="graph-wrap">
    <div class="graph-header">📈 Live CPS Graph</div>
    <canvas id="click-graph"></canvas>
  </div>

  <div class="history-section">
    <div class="section-label">Your Recent Scores</div>
    <div id="history-list"><p class="history-empty">No scores yet — take your first test!</p></div>
  </div>

  <!-- Result Overlay -->
  <div id="result-overlay">
    <div class="result-card">
      <div class="result-new-best" id="new-best" style="display:none">🎉 New Personal Best!</div>
      <div class="result-cps" id="res-cps">0.00</div>
      <div class="result-unit">Clicks Per Second</div>
      <div class="result-rating" id="res-rating">⚡ Fast</div>
      <div class="result-desc"  id="res-desc">Nice work!</div>
      <div class="result-grid">
        <div class="result-cell">
          <div class="result-cell-val" id="res-clicks">0</div>
          <div class="result-cell-lbl">Clicks</div>
        </div>
        <div class="result-cell">
          <div class="result-cell-val" id="res-time">0s</div>
          <div class="result-cell-lbl">Time</div>
        </div>
        <div class="result-cell">
          <div class="result-cell-val" id="res-best">--</div>
          <div class="result-cell-lbl">Best CPS</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="result-btns">
        <button class="btn btn-primary" id="btn-again">Try Again</button>
        <button class="btn btn-ghost"   id="btn-share">Share 📤</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SEO + FAQ -->
  <div class="seo-content">
    <h2>Click Speed Test — Free CPS Test Online</h2>
    <p>
      FastClickTest is the most complete free online click speed test. Whether you want to <strong>test how fast you can click</strong>,
      check <strong>how fast you click your mouse</strong>, or measure your CPS for Minecraft PvP —
      this tool gives you instant, accurate results. No signup, no download, no clutter. Just pick a mode and click.
    </p>

    <h3>How Fast Can You Click? Test It Here</h3>
    <p>
      Ever wondered <em>how fast can I click</em>? Our free click speed test answers that instantly.
      CPS stands for <strong>Clicks Per Second</strong> — the universal measurement of mouse clicking speed.
      To <strong>test how fast you click</strong>, choose a time mode and start clicking the box above.
      Your live CPS score updates every 50 milliseconds. Whether you want to <strong>test how fast u can click</strong>
      or see <strong>how fast do you click</strong> compared to the world average — you'll have your answer in seconds.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Test Your Click Speed</h3>
    <p>
      <strong>How to test click speed:</strong> Select a time mode (1 second, 5 seconds, 10, 15, 30, or 60 seconds),
      then click the box — the timer starts on your first click. Click as fast as you can.
      Your CPS is calculated and saved automatically. Want to <strong>test how fast you can click the spacebar</strong>?
      Visit our dedicated <a href="/spacebar-test">spacebar speed test</a>.
      Want to <strong>test how fast you can click in 60 seconds</strong>? Select the 60s mode above.
      Want to <strong>test to see how fast you click</strong> your mouse on mobile? This tool works on phones too.
    </p>

    <h3>CPS Ratings — How Do You Compare?</h3>
    <p>
      <strong style="color:#f87171">🐢 Turtle (0–2 CPS)</strong> — Just getting started.&nbsp;
      <strong style="color:#fb923c">🐌 Slow (2–4)</strong> — Warming up.&nbsp;
      <strong style="color:#facc15">✌️ Average (4–6)</strong> — Where most casual users land.&nbsp;
      <strong style="color:#4ade80">⚡ Fast (6–8)</strong> — Top 30% of players.&nbsp;
      <strong style="color:#60a5fa">🔥 Insane (8–10)</strong> — Top 10%, competitive gamer level.&nbsp;
      <strong style="color:#c084fc">🚀 Godlike (10–14)</strong> — Elite, top 2%.&nbsp;
      <strong style="color:#fbbf24">👑 World Class (14+)</strong> — World record territory.
      Dylan Allred holds the verified record at <strong>14.1 CPS</strong> sustained for 10 seconds using butterfly clicking.
    </p>

    <h3>Click Speed Test — All Time Modes</h3>
    <p>
      Our <strong>click speed test 1 second</strong> mode captures your absolute peak burst speed.
      The <strong>5-second CPS test</strong> is the global community standard.
      The <strong>click test 30 seconds</strong> and 60-second modes test endurance and consistency.
      The unique <strong>100-click challenge</strong> races you to 100 clicks as fast as possible — divide 100 by
      your time to get average CPS. All modes include a live graph and score history.
    </p>

    <h3>All Click Tests — Right Click, Spacebar, Drag, Kohi, Jitter</h3>
    <p>
      Beyond the standard mouse click speed test, we offer:
      <strong><a href="/right-click-test">Right click CPS test</a></strong> — measures how fast you right-click,
      including a <strong>CPS test right click 1 second</strong> mode.
      <strong><a href="/spacebar-test">Spacebar click speed test</a></strong> — test how fast you can click the spacebar.
      <strong><a href="/drag-click-test">Drag click CPS test</a></strong> — measure your drag clicking technique.
      <strong><a href="/kohi-click-test">Kohi click test</a></strong> — the original Minecraft PvP benchmark.
      <strong><a href="/jitter-click-test">Jitter click test</a></strong> — test your arm-vibration clicking speed.
      <strong><a href="/butterfly-click-test">Butterfly click test</a></strong> — two-finger alternation technique.
      <strong><a href="/reaction-time-test">Click speed test reaction time</a></strong> — measure your reflex speed in ms.
      All free, all instant, no account needed.
    </p>

    <h3>Mouse Click Speed Test — Mobile & Desktop (CPS Test Google Compatible)</h3>
    <p>
      Our <strong>mouse click speed test</strong> works on every device and browser.
      The <strong>CPS test on mobile</strong> registers touch events identically to mouse clicks — tap as fast as you can.
      Results are accurate on Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge.
      This is one of the most <strong>CPS test Google</strong>-indexed tools online, with dedicated pages for every
      clicking technique. For the most accurate <strong>left click CPS test</strong> results, use a desktop with a
      dedicated gaming mouse.
    </p>

    <h3>What is CPS Test Full Form? (Including Medical Use)</h3>
    <p>
      In gaming, <strong>CPS test full form</strong> is <em>Clicks Per Second test</em> — a measure of mouse
      clicking speed. In medical contexts, <strong>CPS test medical</strong> refers to something entirely different:
      the Capsaicin Pain Sensitivity test or similar clinical assessments. This website covers the gaming version only.
      If you are looking for the <strong>CPS test full form in medical</strong> context, please consult a healthcare provider.
    </p>

    <h3>Auto Click Test — Can You Beat an Autoclicker?</h3>
    <p>
      Curious about the <strong>auto click test</strong>? Autoclickers are software tools that simulate mouse clicks
      automatically — they can achieve 20–50+ CPS with no physical effort. Our tool detects and counts all clicks
      including auto-clicks for testing purposes, but auto-clicking is banned on virtually every competitive gaming
      server. The scores on this site are meant to reflect genuine human clicking speed.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Calculate Clicks Per Second (CPS Formula)</h3>
    <p>
      CPS is calculated with a simple formula: <strong>CPS = Total Clicks ÷ Total Time in Seconds</strong>.
      For example, if you click 30 times in 5 seconds, your CPS is 30 ÷ 5 = <strong>6 CPS</strong>.
      FastClickTest does this automatically — you just click and we handle the math in real time.
    </p>

    <h3>Minecraft PvP CPS Categories</h3>
    <p>
      In classic Minecraft 1.8 PvP (no attack cooldown), your clicking speed falls into four tiers
      that affect gameplay differently:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Extremely slow (1–3 CPS)</strong> — You'll struggle to register consistent hits. Only
      useful for chase-hitting with Speed II potions where timing matters more than speed.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Moderately slow (4–7 CPS)</strong> — The sweet spot for accuracy-focused PvP. You can
      aim steadily without hand fatigue, land consistent hits, and still outpace most beginners.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Moderately high (8–13 CPS)</strong> — Competitive territory. You get more hits per
      second but hand stability becomes harder to maintain. This is where most serious players operate.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Extremely fast (14+ CPS)</strong> — Advanced advantage. At this speed, hitting an opponent
      breaks their sprint more frequently, giving you extended reach. This is world-record clicking territory
      and requires techniques like butterfly or drag clicking.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Improve Your Click Speed</h3>
    <p>
      Start with short sessions using 1s and 5s modes to build muscle memory without fatigue. Try
      advanced techniques: <strong>jitter clicking</strong> (tense your forearm muscles),
      <strong>butterfly clicking</strong> (two fingers alternating), or <strong>drag clicking</strong>
      (drag across the button). Use a <strong>gaming mouse</strong> with low actuation force — trackpads
      and regular office mice have far higher resistance. Adjust your <strong>mouse sensitivity</strong>
      settings so clicks register cleanly. Even playing fast-paced shooting games regularly helps train
      your trigger finger and reaction speed. Practice 10–15 minutes daily and track improvement using
      the score history on this page.
    </p>

    <h3>Benefits of Taking the CPS Test</h3>
    <p>
      The click speed test isn't just for gamers. Here's why people across different backgrounds use it:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Stress relief:</strong> Focusing hard on beating your last CPS score naturally takes your
      mind off whatever was stressing you. It's a short, satisfying challenge that resets your mental state.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Improved focus:</strong> Maintaining maximum clicking speed for 10–60 seconds requires
      sustained concentration. Regular practice builds the ability to stay locked in — a skill that
      transfers to work, study, and competitive gaming.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Sparks creativity:</strong> Trying to beat your own score pushes you to experiment with new
      techniques and hand positions. This problem-solving mindset — finding marginal gains — carries over
      into other areas of life.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Builds consistency:</strong> Improving CPS doesn't happen overnight. The discipline of
      returning daily, tracking scores, and making small improvements mirrors the habits behind any
      long-term skill development.
    </p>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="section-label" style="margin-bottom:16px">Frequently Asked Questions</div>

      {[
        [
          'How fast can you click? What is a good CPS score?',
          'The average person clicks at 5–7 CPS during a 5-second test. A score of 6–8 CPS is considered "Fast" — top 30% of all players. Competitive Minecraft players target 8–12 CPS. Anything above 10 CPS requires advanced techniques like jitter or butterfly clicking. The world record is 14.1 CPS sustained over 10 seconds.'
        ],
        [
          'How do I test how fast I can click?',
          'Select a time mode (1s, 5s, 10s etc.), then click the green box above. The timer starts on your first click. Click as fast as possible until time runs out. Your CPS (clicks per second) is calculated and displayed instantly. Your score is saved locally so you can compare future attempts.'
        ],
        [
          'What is the CPS test — and what does CPS stand for?',
          'CPS stands for Clicks Per Second. A CPS test measures how many times you can click your mouse button within a given time frame. It\'s the standard benchmark for mouse clicking speed used in gaming communities, particularly Minecraft PvP, where higher CPS can mean more hits per second.'
        ],
        [
          'What is the Kohi click test?',
          'The Kohi click test originated from the Minecraft PvP server Kohi (now merged with BadLion). Players used it to benchmark their CPS before competitive matches. It\'s functionally identical to a standard CPS test but carries cultural significance in the Minecraft community. We have a dedicated Kohi click test page with separate score tracking.'
        ],
        [
          'What is the right-click CPS test?',
          'The right-click CPS test measures how fast you can right-click your mouse. It works identically to the standard CPS test but tracks right mouse button presses instead. This is useful for games where right-click speed matters. Visit our dedicated right-click test page — the browser\'s context menu is disabled so it doesn\'t interfere.'
        ],
        [
